'''Jimmor Ison''' was a female [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg]] created by the [[AI Project|AI]].

When [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] Commandos went to [[Karlatt]] to destroy the AI, they were accompanied by Ison on her own insistence. She wanted to confront her "father."

The team infiltrated [[Temple Maudit]]. The AI manipulated them subtly, letting Ison, guided by intuition, lead them to the AI's citadel, a giant [[HoloNet transceiver/Legends|HoloNet transceiver]]. The AI then had numerous other cyborgs attack the Rebels, while the AI itself penetrated Ison with filaments in an attempt to take her over.

The Rebels had brought a 7,000-year old secret code they believed would destroy the AI. However, the AI had evolved, and the code was ineffective. In a heroic sacrifice, Ison used the filament connection to destroy both the AI and herself.

This freed the enslaved [[Droid/Legends|droid]] crews of the AI's fleet. The droids immediately abandoned the [[Karlatt system]] and formed the [[Artificial Republic]]. The Republic honored Ison thenceforth as a hero.

